reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 9, 2021
reviews.reviewText: They work fine, but the wire thickness is unimpressive and the pins are very sloppy. Plugging one into the other was surprisingly challenging due to the poor pin aliment and fitment in the holes. If you want to use an ATX breakout board and need an extension, these are great, if your building a computer, maybe keep looking.
